body: Concat can be quantized. Could you please provide a model to repro your issue?
Does Concat in your model only have 1 input? QLinearConcat has a check that requires at least 2 input. We will change it to allow 1 input. However, why do you need a Concat with only 1 input?

issue.title: Quantied model get impossiable to inference result mode.

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body: I have a quantized model which is instance sgmentation. the float32 model can inference can run, but after quantized: ``` quantization/qlinear_concat.cc:36 onnxruntime::contrib::QLinearConcat::QLinearConcat(const onnxruntime::OpKernelInfo &) input_def_count >= 8 && (input_def_count - 2) % 3 == 0 was false. At least two inputs are needed, and each input must be (tensor, scale, zero_point) tuple! ``` this error make my model unable to run. It says some concat issue, how to resolve?? For model information, this might related about the problem:

body:
@yufenglee  thanks for your notice. Let me given more context, I have a sort of complicated model produce `masks`, `scores`, `labels` which is doing instance segmentation, I exported to onnx, and onnx forward correctly, then I want using out to quantize it.

Current situation is, using ort quatize API, I get the model, which the last concat -> QConcat but with only on input.

And the model is unable to inference at all obviously.

So:


1. I now the node is 1 input, but I can not control it, it was generated by ort API;
2. the original concat in flaot32, is just single input since it was doing something like `torch.stack`, and this is again, not controlled by me, it was exported by pytorch.

Anyway to resolve it?
@yufenglee thanks. when will the PR be landed in master?
